g.ns0:text:
$\begin{array}{ll}
A			&: \mbox{number of stages}\\
B			&: \mbox{number of templates per stage}\\
K			&: \mbox{number of clusters= number of equivalent code-vectors}\\
& \mbox{=number of paths through trellis=number of SoC descriptors}=B^A\\ \\


a			&= \{1, 2, \ldots, A\}\\
b			&= \{1, 2, \ldots, B\}\\
k			&= \{1, 2, \ldots, K\}\\ \\


e			&: \mbox{mean squared error between inputs and reconstructed inputs}\\
\mathcal{K}_k			&: \mbox{$k$-th cluster}\\
\hat{m}_k		&: \mbox{$k$-th mean, i.e. $k$-th equivalent code-vector (uses $k$-th SoC descriptor)}\\
\hat{m}_{k,a}		&: \mbox{stage code-vector, $a$-th additive component of $\hat{m}_k$}\\
N_{\mathcal{K}_k} 			&: \mbox{number of input data points that map to the $k$-th cluster}\\ \\


z_{\alpha, \beta}	&: \mbox{stage-codevector at stage $a=\alpha$ and template $b=\beta$}\\
\mathcal{H}_{\alpha, \beta}	&: \mbox{cluster of points that map to $z_{\alpha, \beta}$ stage-codevector}\\
N_{\mathcal{H}_{\alpha, \beta} \cup \mathcal{K}_k}	&: \mbox{number of data points from cluster $\mathcal{K}_k$ that also lie in cluster $\mathcal{H}_{\alpha, \beta}$}\\

\end{array}
$
here, there is a derivative of every equivalent codevector w.r.t. $z_{\alpha, \beta}$

we consider only those data points $x_i$ that map to $z_{\alpha, \beta}$, i.e. $x_i \in \mathcal{H}_{\alpha, \beta}$, i.e. $\hat{m}_k = \sum\limits_{a=1 \atop a \neq \alpha}^A \hat{m}_{k,a} + z_{\alpha, \beta}$

text.tspan: this step is the same as above
in terms of its component stage-codevectors

- if instead of picking one stage-codevector at a time as in CAC, we pick all same-stage-codevectors, we get a formulation in which we can jointly optimize horizontally along a stage, and vertically as in CAC
- in CAC, optimization is done using a derivative wrt to a single stage-codevector
- the vertical optimization is done separately for every same-stage-codevector
- optimization of one stage-codevector is completely independent of optimizations for other same-stage-codevectors
- with the formulation below, we use GLA on vertical (causal anti-causal) residuals, to optimize all same-stage-codevectors simultaneously
- this is expected to give better results

g.ns0:text: in CAC, of these stage-codevectors, we pick only those that are equal to $z_{\alpha, \beta}$

text.tspan: - as a result of optimizing only one stage-codevector at a time, we optimize in causal anti-causal (vertical) direction only
- i.e., for a given stage, even though all stage-codevectors are held constant, there is no joint optimization between them

$			
\begin{array}{lllll}
e 
&= \sum\limits_{k=1}^{K}\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_k}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_k}}(x_i-\hat{m}_k)^2 	\\ \\



&=
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_1}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_1}}
(x_i-\hat{m}_1)^2p_X(x_i) 	
+	
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_2}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_2}}
(x_i-\hat{m}_2)^2p_X(x_i) 
+
\ldots 	
+	
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_K}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_K}}
(x_i-\hat{m}_K)^2p_X(x_i)	\\ \\




&=
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_1}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_1}}
\bigg(x_i-\sum\limits_{a=1}^A \hat{m}_{1,a}\bigg)^2p_X(x_i) 	
+	
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_2}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_2}}
\bigg(x_i-\sum\limits_{a=1}^A \hat{m}_{2,a}\bigg)^2p_X(x_i) 
+
\ldots 	
+	
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_K}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_K}}
\bigg(x_i-\sum\limits_{a=1}^A \hat{m}_{K,a}\bigg)^2p_X(x_i)	\\ \\ \\





&=
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_1}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_1}}
\bigg(x_i-\sum\limits_{a=1 \atop a \neq \alpha}^A \hat{m}_{1,a} - \hat{m}_{1,\alpha}\bigg)^2p_X(x_i) 	
+	
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_2}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_2}}
\bigg(x_i-\sum\limits_{a=1 \atop a \neq \alpha}^A \hat{m}_{2,a} - \hat{m}_{2,\alpha}\bigg)^2p_X(x_i) 
+
\ldots 	
+	
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_K}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_K}}
\bigg(x_i-\sum\limits_{a=1 \atop a \neq \alpha}^A \hat{m}_{K,a} - \hat{m}_{K,\alpha}\bigg)^2p_X(x_i)	\\ \\ \\ \\ \\





&=
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_1}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_1}}
(g_i - \hat{m}_{1,\alpha})^2p_X(x_i) 	
+	
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_2}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_2}}
(g_i - \hat{m}_{2,\alpha})^2p_X(x_i) 
+
\ldots 	
+	
\sum\limits_{i=1 \atop x_i \in \mathcal{K}_K}^{N_{\mathcal{K}_K}}
(g_i - \hat{m}_{K,\alpha})^2p_X(x_i)	\\



\end{array}
$
here we are optimizing all stage-codevectors at stage $\alpha$
